Pre-Game Insights: England and Scotland shared a point each after their match at the same venue was washed out on Tuesday.
England are fourth in Group B with one point, while Australia are second with two points after beating Oman in their opener.
A defeat to ODI world champions Australia on Saturday could leave England’s Super Eight qualification in jeopardy.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The group is led by Scotland, who have three points from two games, while Namibia are third with two points from two games and Oman sit at the bottom after losing two games.
